  <preface xml:id="meta_frontmatter-preface">
    <title>Preface</title>
    <p>
      <em>Think Bayes</em> is an introduction to Bayesian statistics using computational methods.
      This book uses Python code instead of mathematical notation to explain Bayesian statistical concepts.
    </p>
    <p>
      The premise of this book, and the other books in the <em>Think X</em> series, is that if you know how to program,
      you can use that skill to learn other topics. By using code to explore statistical concepts,
      you can develop your intuition and test your understanding.
    </p>
    <p>
      This is a <url href="https://pretextbook.org" visual="pretextbook.org">PreTeXt</url> adaptation of
